The Police in Mankweng outside Polokwane are
investigating two counts of culpable homicide after the death of two gogos. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said it is
alleged that two pensioners aged 60 and 76, were crossing the R71 road between
Polokwane and Tzaneen near Nobody village when they were knocked down by a bakkie
and died instantly. Both the deceased were enroute to a pension pay point. While the 76-year-old gogo has already been identified, the 60-year-old is still unknown. Anyone who can assist the Police in the identification of
the deceased, may contact Captain Kanyane on 082 729 1042 or to go to Mankweng
Police Station. Ngoepe said the circumstances around this accident is
subject to the ongoing Police investigations. 